						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab near the Bhajanakaṭṭe.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI (Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This badly mutilated inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva</hi> whom the inscription also calls Vikramāditya. As most of the inscription is effaced, the contents of the record cannot be made out. The two <hi rend="bold">Six-hundreds</hi> (division) and <hi rend="bold">Banavāsi Twelve-thousand</hi> are mentioned. The name of the governor of these divisions is lost.</p>						

						</summary>
